<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Ellystra on 03-31-2002 11:05 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Simple as this - some servers have been able to maintain and respect a list. I stress - SOME SERVERS.

For instance - on Bertoxx - it's a damn free for all... uber guilds have like 9 billion level 60's logged nearby - and go play twinks. Then the minute someone gets word that Rage is up - they all log in and form into predefined groups which were already buffed before logging. It makes it impossible to complete it.

And woe to those able to get their forces there in time to actually engage Ragefire - they have it kill stolen right from under their noses thanks to Verant's wonderful "DD crits" for Wizzes (and other such classes) who stand there and nuke the crap out of RF (for 3K + dmg per spellcast). I know - it happened to a close friend of mine. Verant's response you ask? Tough sh*t because you didn't have enough folks there to keep him from being KS'd.

In retrospect.... I've been waiting 11 months to get Ragefire to finish off the epic... in light of the recent changes and KS fests and fighting that's been created - I highly doubt I'll ever finish off the quest.

*sigh* If you're out there watching this thread Verant - you royally f*cked up and need re-evaluate and change this quest again - because all you did was make a bad situation intolerable.

